critique: This document is a revocation of a previous executive order regarding public lands in Wyoming. It revokes Executive Order No. 5603, which withdrew public lands in a specific township pending a resurvey. The revocation is contingent upon the official filing of the plat of resurvey. There is no information to suggest a stance on immigration, executive power, federalism, national security vs. civil liberties, economic regulation, or social inclusion. The document appears neutral regarding ideological tilt.
